[SN]TITLE[SN]
Bomb disposal team called to toy grenade in Coatbridge

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A bomb alert in Coatbridge which resulted in some homes being evacuated was caused by a toy grenade.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Bomb disposal experts were called to the North Lanarkshire town's Burnbank Street after workmen discovered a suspected explosive device on Friday.
Homes in the street were evacuated and nearby roads closed off as a precaution while the incident was dealt with.
Police said the item found by workmen was a toy grenade and local roads had re-opened and residents returned home.
